column3: “This strain is lovely. My girlfriend and I both enjoy smoking it, and it enhances our sexual vibrations after smoking. The White Tahoe Cooks are a mans best friend... fellas”

“Picked this beauty up at Patient Care First in Ceres, California. They’ve got the best stuff for bomb prices. I picked up this strain at $10 for a gram of their exotics because it just looked top notch, and I mean look at its lineage. You can’t go wrong.

I vaped on this with the MigVapor Sub Herb at 22 watts. One small vape bowl and I was at a solid 8/10 within ten minutes from the first pull. Full body warmth and r...”

“Lime green nugs with fat orange hairs, good trich development and moderate to heavy crystal cover. Medium resin content, smokes very well. 
The high left nothing to be desired. Well balanced between body and mind. Found myself spacing out trying to order a sandwich much to the chagrin of the sandwich maker. I wish I could give it 4.5 stars.”
“High was like a stronger version of thin mints to me, taste was closer to the white. Was great in a joint.”

“absolutely one of the best flowers on the market now. my favorite.  I give it 4 out of 5 only because of the aroma.  it's very fuely. so if you were to need to hide for any reason.  it's almost Impossible”
“This strain has by far been the best for sleep and appetite stimulation for me. It smells great, has a beautiful frost to it, and really goes a long way. Be careful though, it can be VERY sedating.”

“Spectacular! Was recommended by my budtender but, I actually went to purchase this strain, based on the reviews left here. I must say... I’m VERY impressed! Great, mellow, balanced high. ZAPPED my nausea in an instant and, relaxed me from head to toe. All of my pain melted away. (I was about a 7/10 pain scale, pre-smoke) I felt amazing after just a few moments. 15 minutes later, I’m about a 2/10, zero nausea and, in ...”
“this is one off the best flowers I've tried it was coated in that fine white goodness I would definitely get it again”
“this is one off the best flowers I've tried it was coated in that fine white goodness I would definitely get it again”

“Got WTC at commencement bay in fife WA. Gold leaf does a photogenic version that gistens trich listing the thc at 22%. Lime to emerald green fat nugs and leaves with moderate amount of long neon orange hairs. Smells like white glue. Smokes clean and smooth all the way through. Little cough that lags. Effects come on quick with  a massive relaxation, sedation, a little happiness and creativity.

Highly recommend, will...”

“White Tahoe Cookies has become my current favorite hybrid indica strain. I picked up some flower of this bud a week ago and the potency is unmatched. A little quickly goes a long way, which I always appreciate.

The high is a heavy one, consuming your body with relief and a bit of tingly feeling. The head high is mostly euphoric and relaxing. Great for melting away stress at any time of the day.”

“A clean heavy hybrid that is not panicky or claustrophobic. Bang for your buck. Strong. Fun, uplifting, I feel like organizing my schedule. No munchies, no appetite anymore actually and I was hungry before. Seems functional 
I love it”

“This was a Budtender's suggestion; High THC, great aroma and sweet looking nugs.  

Worthy of trying again; but its a Sativa to me. 

Backstory:
Got terminated; wanted that Netflix In the couch moment.

Instead; I get Netflix and applied for 3 new job ops.  

yeah, it got me thinking and then some.  Sativa!

ok, maybe its a FIVE star”
“Sativa effects seem to last a lot longer than Indica effects. Nose is 5/5. Potency is 3.5/5. Buds themselves are 4/5.”
“good high, bad paranoia, and morning head ache like i drank a 6 pack of bud.”
“Great strain! Tastes good, looks good, and feels good.”
“Sativa effects seem to last a lot longer than Indica effects. Nose is 5/5. Potency is 3.5/5. Buds themselves are 4/5.”

“This strain taste like skunky earth, heavily accented with a berries, cream and licorice after taste. Upon the onset of affect, I noticed myself feeling warm, as if I was being covered with a blanket. The high mainly stays in the body. In my opinion it’s best consumed through a volcano.”
“Been on the white tahoe cookies in the flower form and omg that flavor is insane. Great for chillin' or trying to curb out look no further that white tahoe cookies get you some asap!!”
“Two hitter quitter”
“Very high. Very cerebral. Wish it would have been more of a body high. This is good weed if you want to go down a philosophical rabbit hole. Not so good for depression or insomnia.”

“Smoked this for chronic back pain, and definitely noticed a difference. A very nice body high that leaves your mind relaxed, but in high doses can cause a little paranoia. Great for sex. Leads into sleep well.”
“Dense and gorgeous, frosty buds. Smells very sweet, yet gassy. Tastes about the same, thick on the exhale. Nice, well rounded high. This farm knocked this one out of the park.”

“Smoked again, while sleep-deprived and doing chores.
Felt energized, but paranoid. Not anxious, but distracted. Light headed feeling, with little body high too. Skunky smell”

“Smoked again, while sleep-deprived and doing chores.
Felt energized, but paranoid. Not anxious, but distracted. Light headed feeling, with little body high too. Skunky smell”

“This strain taste like skunky earth, heavily accented with a berries, cream and licorice after taste. Upon the onset of affect, I noticed myself feeling warm, as if I was being covered with a blanket. The high mainly stays in the body. In my opinion it’s best consumed through a volcano.”

“Heard goof things about this strain, first time trying it was last night, me and my buddy split a small bowl and that was all we needed. Great strain for just chillin, I finished the little bit left in my grinder when i got home and that was it, I was done. Easily one of my new favorite strains, glad you can get that kind of high on very little. Strong stuff and still leaves you functional if you don't smoke a ton of...”
“ohhhhh shit!!!! Really good!!!I am a fan of anything from white genetics.So matching White with Tahoe OG is a perfect match made in Cannabis Heaven.Great taste,smell and appearance.”
“Been on the white tahoe cookies in the flower form and omg that flavor is insane. Great for chillin' or trying to curb out look no further that white tahoe cookies get you some asap!!”

“Frackin eh this is good! My tender thankfully recommended this to me today, girl nailed it. BEAUTIFUL buds that smell heavenly!! After 2 bowls I'm good. That's saying something for someone who usually needs 2 grams. Must try. Anxiety is gone I'm feeling happy and blissful. I love you White Tahoe Cookies”
“Exceptional strain for the night man I smoke this and man I got a whiff of release like you wouldn’t believe”

“I was looking to scramble my troubled mind, and this is the medicine I took. Two hits brings on a warm, fuzzy fog that slows down time and softens edges. Makes me want to play music. Makes me want to put the laundry in the dryer. Makes me want to lie down on the couch to do homework and I end up writing this review instead. 
    It comes on fairly quick, like a sneaker wave, and settles in the valley of your mind for...”
“I like it.  Makes me feel good, nice body high”
“this is one of my favorite strains. its relaxing, good for socializing and couch surfing.  The girl friend gets tingles and it perks up her sexual appetite.”

“One of the best 2018 strains out there. My husband was speechless when it came to how good this one is. And he’s a 24/7 smoker. It’s very hard to impress his green palate-but this one did the trick. Be careful if you’re a novice smoker.”

“Taste was A1, it was a great balanced head and body high, smooth hits, i would definetly recommed this strain. I was too lazy to keep my eyes open, so i just listened to podcasts and i felt i absorb information pretty good while laying down being relaxed until i knocked. Strong smell. Great after a long day. Overall A1”
“it looks amazing, and tastes great. Super stoney high, tastes musky and sweet.”
“amazing. great for end of the night or if you had a long day”

“Frosty dark purpleish nugs that reek of that sweet earthy cookies note with some hashy berry undertones from the Tahoe and White. The high is mindnumbing, perfect for vegging out in front of the tv after work. Definitely not a daytime strain, the intoxicating effects on the mind make it difficult to focus on tedious tasks such as housework and the body high leaves you in a lazy daze. I say these things as positives t...”
“Calming but not couch potato”
“this stain is easy to quit. usually i will wake up and within an hour or 2 i want to smoke but this strain doesn't. its a easy high that isn't additive.”
“Fire! Anything cookies" you can't go wrong. Always Stony
column4: no wonder rapper Berner smokes lots of cookies!”"

column3: “It’s great for insomnia! I got very tired after smoking it. Not a good strain if you want to good anything done.”
“good stuff. bready gassy taste and smell. a bit too heady for me.”
“Some of the best weed I’ve smoked. The buds were completely coated in crystals. Super relaxing and euphoric. Made me want to spend intimate time with my wife.”

“If you manage to get yourself some of this exotic REAL cookies you’re one lucky feller.

Type of weed you save a few nugs of and put in a jar for a raining day. 

5/5 Best cookies”
“unicorn of the 🍪 family.... super tasty and sedaring. blunts, joints, pipes, bongs: there are no wrong choices, just which is next...”

“Top 100 of All Time Best!

Simply spectacular in every way.”

“For me it was a good body high. I agree,it sedated me. Very good for doing nothing, relaxing watching TV. It was a smooth toke. I really enjoyed this. I recommend this for bed time, or just a lazy day. I will definitely get this again”
“I absolutely LOVE this strain. It's a relaxing, cuddly kind of high that gets me ready for bed every night. And the dreams I have with this stuff are stellar. Definitely recommend.”

“Works really good for pain. I have 5 things that cause chronic pain. This is by far the best I’ve tired for my pain and anxiety I have from PTSD  I absolutely hate big pharma pills. They don’t cure anything only treat symptoms. I have osteoarthritis all over and my inflammation level is only 23% I KNOW it’s from the healing properties of this plant. Love the whole body and relaxed mind it gives. Trust me no pill can ...”
“I felt like my whole body was being tickled by a million tiny elf fingers!”
